69846.name: Abomination
69846.flavorText: Abominations enjoy Fresh Meat and long walks on the beach.

69761.name: Abusive Sergeant
69761.text: Battlecry: Give a minion +2 Attack this turn.
69761.flavorText: ADD ME TO YOUR DECK, MAGGOT!

69809.name: Acolyte of Pain
69809.text: Whenever this minion takes damage, draw a card.
69809.flavorText: He trained when he was younger to be an acolyte of joy, but things didn’t work out like he thought they would.

70078.name: Al'Akir the Windlord
70078.flavorText: He is the weakest of the four Elemental Lords. And the other three don't let him forget it.

69808.name: Alarm-o-Bot
69808.text: At the start of your turn, swap this minion with a random one in your hand.

69941.name: Aldor Peacekeeper
69941.text: Battlecry: Change an enemy minion's Attack to 1.
69941.flavorText: The Aldor hate two things: the Scryers and smooth jazz.

69977.name: Alexstrasza
69977.text: Battlecry: Set a hero's remaining Health to 15.
69977.flavorText: Alexstrasza the Life-Binder brings life and hope to everyone. Except Deathwing. And Malygos. And Nekros.

69947.name: Amani Berserker
69947.flavorText: If an Amani berserker asks "Joo lookin' at me?!", the correct response is "Nah, mon".

68331.name: Ancestral Healing
68331.text: Restore a minion to full Health and give it Taunt.
68331.flavorText: I personally prefer some non-ancestral right-the-heck-now healing, but maybe that is just me.

69749.name: Ancestral Spirit
69749.text: Choose a minion. When that minion is destroyed, return it to the battlefield.
69749.flavorText: It was just a flesh wound.

69832.name: Ancient Brewmaster
69832.text: Battlecry: Return a friendly minion from the battlefield to your hand.
69832.flavorText: Most pandaren say his brew tastes like yak. But apparently that's a compliment.

70036.name: Ancient Mage
70036.flavorText: Sometimes he forgets and just wanders into someone else's game.

69826.name: Ancient Watcher
69826.flavorText: Why do its eyes seem to follow you as you walk by?

70077.name: Ancient of Lore
70077.text: Choose One - Draw 2 cards; or Restore 5 Health.
70077.flavorText: Go ahead, carve your initials in him.

69875.name: Ancient of War
69875.flavorText: Young Night Elves love to play "Who can get the Ancient of War to Uproot?" You lose if you get crushed to death.

69811.name: Angry Chicken
69811.flavorText: There is no beast more frightening (or ridiculous) than a fully enraged chicken.

68529.name: Animal Companion
68529.flavorText: You could summon Misha, Leokk, or Huffer! Huffer is more trouble than he's worth.

69949.name: Arathi Weaponsmith
69949.flavorText: 50% off fist weapons, limited time only!

68323.name: Arcane Explosion
68323.text: Deal 1 damage to all enemy minions.
68323.flavorText: This spell is much better than Arcane Implosion.

69841.name: Arcane Golem
69841.text: Charge. Battlecry: Give your opponent a Mana Crystal.
69841.flavorText: Having Arcane golems at home really classes up the place, and as a bonus they are great conversation pieces.

68321.name: Arcane Intellect
68321.flavorText: Playing this card makes you SMARTER. And let's face it: we could all stand to be a little smarter.

68457.name: Arcane Missiles
68457.text: Deal 3 damage randomly split among all enemy characters.
68457.flavorText: You'd think you'd be able to control your missiles a little better since you're a powerful mage and all.

68434.name: Arcane Shot
68434.flavorText: Magi conjured arcane arrows to sell to hunters, until hunters learned just enough magic to do it themselves. The resulting loss of jobs sent Stormwind into a minor recession.

68377.name: Arcanite Reaper
68377.flavorText: No… actually you should fear the Reaper.

68393.name: Archmage
68393.flavorText: You earn the title of Archmage when you can destroy anyone who calls you on it.

69975.name: Archmage Antonidas
69975.text: Whenever you cast a spell, add a 'Fireball' spell to your hand.
69975.flavorText: Antonidas was the Grand Magus of the Kirin Tor, and Jaina's mentor. This was a big step up from being Grand Magus of Jelly Donuts.

69835.name: Argent Commander
69835.flavorText: The Argent Dawn stands vigilant against the Scourge, as well as people who cut in line at coffee shops.

69936.name: Argent Protector
69936.flavorText: "I'm not saying you can dodge fireballs. I'm saying with this shield, you won't have to."

69810.name: Argent Squire
69810.flavorText: "I solemnly swear to uphold the Light, purge the world of darkness, and to eat only burritos." - The Argent Dawn Oath

69950.name: Armorsmith
69950.text: Whenever a friendly minion takes damage, gain 1 Armor.
69950.flavorText: She accepts guild funds for repairs!

68354.name: Assassin's Blade
68354.flavorText: Guaranteed to have been owned by a real assassin. Certificate of authenticity included.

68352.name: Assassinate
68352.flavorText: If you don't want to be assassinated, move to the Barrens and change your name. Good luck!

70039.name: Auchenai Soulpriest
70039.text: Your cards and powers that restore Health now deal damage instead.
70039.flavorText: The Auchenai know the end is coming, but they're not sure when.

69943.name: Avenging Wrath
69943.text: Deal 8 damage randomly split among all enemy characters.
69943.flavorText: Wham! Wham! Wham! Wham! Wham! Wham! Wham! Wham!

69907.name: Azure Drake
69907.flavorText: They initially planned to be the Beryl or Cerulean drakes, but those felt a tad too pretentious.

68348.name: Backstab
68348.text: Deal 2 damage to an undamaged minion.
68348.flavorText: It's funny how often yelling "Look over there!" gets your opponent to turn around.

69924.name: Bane of Doom
69924.text: Deal 2 damage to a character. If that kills it, summon a random Demon.
69924.flavorText: My advice to you is to avoid Doom, if possible.

69898.name: Baron Geddon
69898.text: At the end of your turn, deal 2 damage to ALL other characters.
69898.flavorText: Baron Geddon was Ragnaros's foremost lieutenant, until he got FIRED.

69946.name: Battle Rage
69946.text: Draw a card for each damaged friendly character.
69946.flavorText: "You won't like me when I'm angry."

69970.name: Bestial Wrath
69970.text: Give a Beast +2 Attack and Immune this turn.
69970.flavorText: The seething wrath is just beneath the surface. Beneath that is wild abandon, followed by slight annoyance.

69854.name: Betrayal
69854.text: Force an enemy minion to deal its damage to the minions next to it.
69854.flavorText: Everyone has a price. Gnomes, for example, can be persuaded by stuffed animals and small amounts of chocolate.

69807.name: Big Game Hunter
69807.text: Battlecry: Destroy a minion with 7 or more Attack.
69807.flavorText: Mere devilsaurs no longer excite him. Soon he'll be trying to catch Onyxia with only a dull Krol Blade.

69982.name: Bite
69982.text: Give your hero +4 Attack this turn. Gain 4 Armor.

69766.name: Blade Flurry
69766.text: Destroy your weapon and deal its damage to all enemies.
69766.flavorText: "Look, it's not just about waving daggers around really fast. It's a lot more complicated than that." - Shan, Rogue Trainer

69935.name: Blessed Champion
69935.flavorText: This card causes double the trouble AND double the fun.

68364.name: Blessing of Kings
68364.flavorText: Given the number of kings who have been assassinated, are you sure you want their blessing?

68359.name: Blessing of Might
68359.flavorText: "As in, you MIGHT want to get out of my way." - Toad Mackle, recently buffed.

69937.name: Blessing of Wisdom
69937.text: Choose a minion. Whenever it attacks, draw a card.
69937.flavorText: Apparently with wisdom comes the knowledge that you should probably be attacking every turn.

69747.name: Blizzard
69747.text: Deal 2 damage to all enemy minions and Freeze them.
69747.flavorText: This spell can be very Entertaining.

69751.name: Blood Imp
69751.text: Stealth. At the end of your turn, give another random friendly minion +1 Health.
69751.flavorText: Imps are content to hide and viciously taunt everyone nearby.

70038.name: Blood Knight
70038.text: Battlecry: All minions lose Divine Shield. Gain +3/+3 for each Shield lost.
70038.flavorText: The Blood Knights get their holy powers from the Sunwell, which you should NOT bathe in.

68336.name: Bloodlust
68336.text: Give your minions +3 Attack this turn.

69813.name: Bloodmage Thalnos
69813.flavorText: He's in charge of the Annual Scarlet Monastery Blood Drive!

70089.name: Bloodsail Corsair
70089.text: Battlecry: Remove 1 Durability from your opponent's weapon.
70089.flavorText: Every pirate uses the same four digits to access Automated Gold Dispensers. It's called the "Pirate's Code".

70082.name: Bloodsail Raider
70082.text: Battlecry: Gain Attack equal to the Attack of your weapon.
70082.flavorText: "I only plunder on days that end in 'y'."

68398.name: Bluegill Warrior
68398.flavorText: He just wants a hug. A sloppy... slimy... hug.

68402.name: Booty Bay Bodyguard
68402.flavorText: You can hire him... until someone offers him enough gold to turn on you.

68406.name: Boulderfist Ogre
68406.flavorText: "ME HAVE GOOD STATS FOR THE COST"

69952.name: Brawl
69952.text: Destroy all minions except one. (chosen randomly)
69952.flavorText: Do you know the first rule of Brawl Club?

69842.name: Cabal Shadow Priest
69842.text: Battlecry: Take control of an enemy minion that has 2 or less Attack.
69842.flavorText: You never know who may be secretly working for the Cabal....

69851.name: Cairne Bloodhoof
69851.flavorText: Cairne was killed by Garrosh, so... don't put this guy in a Warrior deck. It's pretty insensitive.

70088.name: Captain Greenskin
70088.flavorText: He was this close to piloting a massive juggernaut into Stormwind Harbor. If it weren't for those pesky kids!

68549.name: Captain's Parrot
68549.text: Battlecry: Draw a Pirate from your deck.
68549.flavorText: Pirates and Parrots go together like Virmen and Carrots.

70031.name: Cenarius
70031.text: Choose One - Give your other minions +2/+2; or Summon two 2/2 Treants with Taunt.
70031.flavorText: Yes, he's a demigod. No, he doesn't need to wear a shirt.

68371.name: Charge
68371.text: Give a friendly minion +2 Attack and Charge.
68371.flavorText: "Guys! Guys! Slow down!" - some kind of non-warrior minion

68400.name: Chillwind Yeti
68400.flavorText: He always dreamed of coming down from the mountains and opening a noodle shop, but he never got the nerve.

68307.name: Claw
68307.text: Give your hero +2 Attack this turn. Gain 2 Armor.
68307.flavorText: The claw decides who will stay and who will go.

68378.name: Cleave
68378.text: Deal 2 damage to two random enemy minions.
68378.flavorText: Hey you two…could you stand next to each other for a second…

69752.name: Cold Blood
69752.text: Give a minion +2 Attack. Combo: +4 Attack instead.
69752.flavorText: "I'm cold blooded, check it and see!"

69830.name: Coldlight Oracle
69830.flavorText: They can see the future. In that future both players draw more cards. Spoooky.

69849.name: Coldlight Seer
69849.flavorText: The Coldlight murlocs reside in the darkest pits of the Abyssal Depths. So no, there's no getting away from murlocs.

70094.name: Commanding Shout
70094.text: Your minions can't be reduced below 1 Health this turn. Draw a card.
70094.flavorText: "Shout! Shout! Let it all out!" - Advice to warriors-in-training

69855.name: Conceal
69855.text: Give your minions Stealth until your next turn.
69855.flavorText: Rogues conceal everything but their emotions. You can't get 'em to shut up about feelings.

69904.name: Cone of Cold
69904.text: Freeze a minion and the minions next to it, and deal 1 damage to them.
69904.flavorText: Magi of the Kirin Tor were casting Cubes of Cold for many years before Cones came into fashion some 90 years ago.

68366.name: Consecration
68366.flavorText: Consecrated ground glows with Holy energy. But it smells a little, too.

68407.name: Core Hound
68407.flavorText: You don’t tame a Core Hound. You just train it to eat someone else before it eats you.

68344.name: Corruption
68344.text: Choose an enemy minion. At the start of your turn, destroy it.
68344.flavorText: It starts with stealing a pen from work, and before you know it, BOOOM! Corrupted!

69908.name: Counterspell
69908.text: Secret: When your opponent casts a spell, Counter it.
69908.flavorText: What's the difference between a mage playing with Counterspell and a mage who isn't? The mage who isn't is getting Pyroblasted in the face.

69834.name: Crazed Alchemist
69834.text: Battlecry: Swap the Attack and Health of a minion.
69834.flavorText: "You'll love my new recipe!" he says... especially if you're not happy with your current number of limbs.

70045.name: Cruel Taskmaster
70045.text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it +2 Attack.
70045.flavorText: "I'm going to need you to come in on Sunday." - Cruel Taskmaster

70041.name: Cult Master
70041.text: After a friendly minion dies, draw a card.
70041.flavorText: She may be an evil cult master, but she still calls her parents once a week.

68476.name: Dalaran Mage
68476.flavorText: You don't see a lot of Dalaran warriors.

69827.name: Dark Iron Dwarf
69827.text: Battlecry: Give a minion +2 Attack this turn.
69827.flavorText: Guardians of Dark Iron Ore. Perhaps the most annoying ore, given where you have to forge it.

68425.name: Darkscale Healer
68425.text: Battlecry: Restore 2 Health to all friendly characters.
68425.flavorText: Healing is just something she does in her free time. It's more of a hobby really.

68349.name: Deadly Poison
68349.flavorText: Rogues guard the secrets to poison-making carefully, lest magi start incorporating poison into their spells. Poisonbolt? Rain of Poison? Poison Elemental? Nobody wants that.

70056.name: Deadly Shot
70056.flavorText: Our ballista operator is effective, but not picky.

70093.name: Deathwing
70093.text: Battlecry: Destroy all other minions and discard your hand.
70093.flavorText: Once a noble dragon known as Neltharion, Deathwing lost his mind and shattered Azeroth before finally being defeated. Daddy issues?

69843.name: Defender of Argus
69843.flavorText: You wouldn’t think that Argus would need this much defending. But it does.

69857.name: Defias Ringleader
69857.flavorText: He stole the deed to town years ago, so technically the town is his. He just calls people Scrub to be mean.

69848.name: Demolisher
69848.text: At the start of your turn, deal 2 damage to a random enemy.
69848.flavorText: Laying siege isn't fun for anyone. It's not even all that effective, now that everyone has a flying mount.

70042.name: Demonfire
70042.text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. If it’s a friendly Demon, give it +2/+2 instead.
70042.flavorText: Demonfire is like regular fire except for IT NEVER STOPS BURNING HELLLPPP

69870.name: Dire Wolf Alpha
69870.flavorText: We are pretty excited about the upcoming release of Dire Wolf Beta, just repost this sign for a chance at a key.

69932.name: Divine Favor
69932.text: Draw cards until you have as many in hand as your opponent.
69932.flavorText: This is not just a favor, but a divine one, like helping someone move a couch with a fold out bed!

68536.name: Divine Spirit
68536.flavorText: Double the trouble. Double the fun!

69917.name: Doomguard
69917.flavorText: Summoning a doomguard is risky. Someone is going to die.

69981.name: Doomhammer
69981.flavorText: Orgrim Doomhammer gave this legendary weapon to Thrall. His name is a total coincidence.

70085.name: Doomsayer
70085.text: At the start of your turn, destroy ALL minions.
70085.flavorText: He's almost been right so many times. He was sure it was coming during the Cataclysm.

68439.name: Dragonling Mechanic
68439.flavorText: She is still working on installing the rocket launcher add-on for Mr. Bitey.

68342.name: Drain Life
68342.text: Deal 2 damage. Restore 2 Health to your hero.
68342.flavorText: "I've just sucked one year of your life away."

70086.name: Dread Corsair
70086.text: Taunt Costs (1) less per Attack of your weapon.
70086.flavorText: "Yarrrr" is a pirate word that means "Greetings, milord."

68346.name: Dread Infernal
68346.text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to ALL other characters.
68346.flavorText: "INFERNOOOOOOOOOO!" - Jaraxxus, Eredar Lord of the Burning Legion

69872.name: Druid of the Claw
69872.flavorText: Cat or Bear? Cat or Bear?! I just cannot CHOOSE!

69894.name: Dust Devil
69894.flavorText: Westfall is full of dust devils. And buzzards. And crazed golems. And pirates. Why does anyone live here?

69965.name: Eaglehorn Bow
69965.text: Whenever a Secret is revealed, gain +1 Durability.
69965.flavorText: First Lesson: Put the pointy end in the other guy.

69895.name: Earth Shock
69895.text: Silence a minion, then deal 1 damage to it.
69895.flavorText: Earth Shock? Shouldn't it be "Azeroth Shock"?

69754.name: Earthen Ring Farseer
69754.flavorText: He can see really far, and he doesn't use a telescope like those filthy pirates.

70053.name: Edwin VanCleef
70053.text: Combo: Gain +2/+2 for each card played earlier this turn.
70053.flavorText: He led the Stonemasons in the reconstruction of Stormwind, and when the nobles refused to pay, he founded the Defias Brotherhood to, well, deconstruct Stormwind.

68550.name: Elite Tauren Chieftain
68550.text: Battlecry: Give both players the power to ROCK! (with a Power Chord card)
68550.flavorText: He's looking for a drummer. The current candidates are: Novice Engineer, Sen'jin Shieldmasta', and Ragnaros the Firelord.

68403.name: Elven Archer
68403.flavorText: Don't bother asking her out on a date. She'll shoot you down.

69874.name: Emperor Cobra
69874.text: Destroy any minion damaged by this minion.
69874.flavorText: The Sholazar Basin is home to a lot of really horrible things. If you're going to visit, wear bug spray. And plate armor.

70057.name: Equality
70057.text: Change the Health of ALL minions to 1.
70057.flavorText: We are all special unique snowflakes... with 1 Health.

69903.name: Ethereal Arcanist
69903.text: If you control a Secret at the end of your turn, gain +2/+2.
69903.flavorText: The ethereals are wrapped in cloth to give form to their non-corporeal bodies. Also because it's nice and soft.

69853.name: Eviscerate
69853.flavorText: There is a high cost to Eviscerating your opponent. You might tweak your elbow! That really hurts!

69966.name: Explosive Shot
69966.text: Deal 5 damage to a minion and 2 damage to adjacent ones.
69966.flavorText: Pull the pin, count to 5, then shoot. Then duck.

70050.name: Explosive Trap
70050.text: Secret: When your hero is attacked, deal 2 damage to all enemies.
70050.flavorText: It traps your food AND cooks it for you!

69858.name: Eye for an Eye
69858.text: Secret: When your hero takes damage, deal that much damage to the enemy hero.
69858.flavorText: Justice sometimes takes the form of a closed fist into a soft cheek.

69980.name: Faceless Manipulator
69980.text: Battlecry: Choose a minion and become a copy of it.
69980.flavorText: The Faceless Ones are servants of Yogg-Saron, and they feed on fear. Right now they are feeding on your fear of accidentally disenchanting all your good cards.

70087.name: Faerie Dragon
70087.flavorText: Adorable. Immune to Magic. Doesn't pee on the rug. The perfect pet!

68444.name: Fan of Knives
68444.text: Deal 1 damage to all enemy minions. Draw a card.
68444.flavorText: I wouldn't say I LOVE knives, but I'm definitely a fan.

69750.name: Far Sight
69750.text: Draw a card. That card costs (3) less.
69750.flavorText: Drek'thar can't see, but he can see. You know what I mean? It's ok if you don't.

69913.name: Felguard
69913.text: Taunt Battlecry: Destroy one of your Mana Crystals.
69913.flavorText: Yes, he'll fight for you. BUT HE'S NOT GOING TO LIKE IT.

68460.name: Felstalker
68460.flavorText: This puppy chews up cards instead of shoes.

69745.name: Fen Creeper
69745.flavorText: He used to be called Bog Beast, but it confused people because he wasn't an actual beast. Boom, New Name!

69897.name: Feral Spirit
69897.flavorText: Spirit wolves are like regular wolves with pom-poms.

68375.name: Fiery War Axe
68375.flavorText: During times of tranquility and harmony, this weapon was called by its less popular name, Chilly Peace Axe.

68333.name: Fire Elemental
68333.flavorText: He can never take a bath. Ewww.

68326.name: Fireball
68326.flavorText: This spell is useful for burning things. If you're looking for spells that toast things, or just warm them a little, you're in the wrong place.

69923.name: Flame Imp
69923.flavorText: Imps like being on fire. They just do.

68327.name: Flamestrike
68327.text: Deal 4 damage to all enemy minions.
68327.flavorText: When the ground is on fire, you should not stop, drop, and roll.

68473.name: Flametongue Totem
68473.flavorText: Totemsmiths like to use the rarest woods for their totems. There are even rumors of totems made of Ironbark Protectors.

69969.name: Flare
69969.text: All minions lose Stealth. Destroy all enemy Secrets. Draw a card.
69969.flavorText: Not only does it reveal your enemies, but it's also great for parties!

70101.name: Flesheating Ghoul
70101.text: Whenever a minion dies, gain +1 Attack.
70101.flavorText: 'Flesheating' is an unfair name. It's just that there's not really much else for him to eat.

70981.name: Force of Nature
70981.text: Summon three 2/2 Treants with Charge that die at the end of the turn.
70981.flavorText: "I think I'll just nap under these trees. Wait... AAAAAHHH!" - Blinkfizz, the Unfortunate Gnome

69900.name: Forked Lightning
69900.text: Deal 2 damage to 2 random enemy minions. Overload: (2)
69900.flavorText: If you combine it with Spooned Lightning and Knived Lightning, you have the full dining set.

70051.name: Freezing Trap
70051.text: Secret: When an enemy minion attacks, return it to its owner's hand. It costs (2) more.
70051.flavorText: "Dang, that's cold." - appropriate response to Freezing Trap, or a mean joke.

69906.name: Frost Elemental
69906.flavorText: When a Water elemental and an Ice elemental love each other VERY much...

68324.name: Frost Nova
68324.flavorText: Hey man, that's cold. Literally and metaphorically.

68329.name: Frost Shock
68329.text: Deal 1 damage to an enemy character and Freeze it.

68322.name: Frostbolt
68322.text: Deal 3 damage to a character and Freeze it.
68322.flavorText: It is customary to yell "Chill out!" or "Freeze!" or "Ice ice, baby!" when you play this card.

68382.name: Frostwolf Grunt
68382.flavorText: Grunting is what his father did and his father before that. It's more than just a job.

68411.name: Frostwolf Warlord
68411.text: Battlecry: Gain +1/+1 for each other friendly minion on the battlefield.
68411.flavorText: The Frostwolves are locked in combat with the Stormpike Expedition over control of Alterac Valley. Every attempt at peace-talks has ended with Captain Galvangar killing the mediator.

70046.name: Frothing Berserker
70046.text: Whenever a minion takes damage, gain +1 Attack.
70046.flavorText: He used to work as an accountant before he tried his hand at Berserkering.

69844.name: Gadgetzan Auctioneer
69844.text: Whenever you cast a spell, draw a card.
69844.flavorText: He used to run the black market auction house, but there was just too much violence and he had to move.

68539.name: Gelbin Mekkatorque
68539.flavorText: He's the leader of the gnomes, and an incredible inventor. He's getting better, too; He turns things into chickens WAY less than he used to.

69803.name: Gladiator's Longbow
69803.flavorText: The longbow allows shots to be fired from farther away and is useful for firing on particularly odorous targets.

68391.name: Gnomish Inventor
68391.flavorText: She's never quite sure what she's making, she just knows it's AWESOME!

68298.name: Goldshire Footman
68298.flavorText: If 1/2 minions are all that is defending Goldshire, you would think it would have been overrun years ago.

69956.name: Gorehowl
69956.text: Attacking a minion costs 1 Attack instead of 1 Durability.
69956.flavorText: Grommash Hellscream's famous axe. Somehow this ended up in Prince Malchezaar's possession. Quite the mystery!

68470.name: Grimscale Oracle
68470.flavorText: These are the brainy murlocs. It turns out that doesn’t mean much.

69958.name: Grommash Hellscream
69958.flavorText: Grommash drank the tainted blood of Mannoroth, dooming the orcs to green skin and red eyes! Maybe not his best decision.

70096.name: Gruul
70096.text: At the end of each turn, gain +1/+1 .
70096.flavorText: He's Gruul "the Dragonkiller". He just wanted to cuddle them… he never meant to…

68361.name: Guardian of Kings
68361.flavorText: Holy beings from the beyond are so cliché!

68465.name: Gurubashi Berserker
68465.text: Whenever this minion takes damage, gain +3 Attack.

68367.name: Hammer of Wrath
68367.flavorText: A good paladin has many tools. Hammer of Wrath, Pliers of Vengeance, Hacksaw of Justice, etc.

68464.name: Hand of Protection
68464.flavorText: This spell has been renamed so many times, even paladins don’t know what it should be called anymore.

69974.name: Harrison Jones
69974.text: Battlecry: Destroy your opponent's weapon and draw cards equal to its Durability.
69974.flavorText: “That belongs in the Hall of Explorers!”

69972.name: Harvest Golem
69972.flavorText: "Overheat threshold exceeded. System failure. Wheat clog in port two. Shutting down."

69862.name: Headcrack
69862.text: Deal 2 damage to the enemy hero. Combo: Return this to your hand next turn.
69862.flavorText: When all else fails, nothing beats a swift whack upside the head.

68343.name: Hellfire
68343.flavorText: It's spells like these that make it hard for Warlocks to get decent help.

68373.name: Heroic Strike
68373.text: Give your hero +4 Attack this turn.
68373.flavorText: Really, if you're a hero, this is every strike.

68455.name: Hex
68455.text: Transform a minion into a 0/1 Frog with Taunt.
68455.flavorText: If you Hex a Murloc... it really isn't much of a change, is it?

70097.name: Hogger
70097.text: At the end of your turn, summon a 2/2 Gnoll with Taunt.
70097.flavorText: Hogger is super powerful. If you kill him, it's because he let you.

70061.name: Holy Fire
70061.text: Deal 5 damage. Restore 5 Health to your hero.

68362.name: Holy Light
68362.flavorText: If you are often bathed in Holy Light, you should consider wearing sunscreen.

68299.name: Holy Nova
68299.text: Deal 2 damage to all enemies. Restore 2 Health to all friendly characters.
68299.flavorText: If the Holy Light forsakes you, good luck casting this spell. Also, you're probably a jerk.

68301.name: Holy Smite
68301.flavorText: It doesn't matter how pious you are. Everyone needs a good smiting now and again.

69938.name: Holy Wrath
69938.text: Draw a card and deal damage equal to its Cost.

68426.name: Houndmaster
68426.flavorText: "Who let the dogs out?" he asks. It's rhetorical.

68462.name: Humility
68462.flavorText: This card makes something really damp. Oh wait. That's "Humidity."

68357.name: Hunter's Mark
68357.flavorText: Never play 'Hide and Go Seek' with a Hunter.

69909.name: Ice Barrier
69909.text: Secret: As soon as your hero is attacked, gain 8 Armor.
69909.flavorText: This is Rank 1. Rank 2 is Chocolate Milk Barrier.

69911.name: Ice Block
69911.text: Secret: When your hero takes fatal damage, prevent it and become Immune this turn.
69911.flavorText: Ice is nice, and will suffice!

69748.name: Ice Lance
69748.text: Freeze a character. If it was already Frozen, deal 4 damage instead.
69748.flavorText: The trick is not to break the lance. Otherwise, you have "Ice Pieces." Ice Pieces aren't as effective.

70054.name: Illidan Stormrage
70054.text: Whenever you play a card, summon a 2/1 Flame of Azzinoth.
70054.flavorText: Illidan's brother, Malfurion, imprisoned him beneath Hyjal for 10,000 years. Stormrages are not good at letting go of grudges.

70043.name: Imp Master
70043.text: At the end of your turn, deal 1 damage to this minion and summon a 1/1 Imp.
70043.flavorText: She would enjoy the job a lot more if she just could get the imps to QUIT BITING HER.

69760.name: Injured Blademaster
69760.flavorText: He claims it is an old war wound, but we think he just cut himself shaving.

69746.name: Inner Fire
69746.text: Change a minion's Attack to be equal to its Health.
69746.flavorText: Good idea: Buffing your minions. Bad idea: Starting a conversation in the Barrens.

70047.name: Inner Rage
70047.text: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it +2 Attack.
70047.flavorText: They're only smiling on the outside.

68445.name: Innervate
68445.text: Gain 2 Mana Crystals this turn only.
68445.flavorText: Some druids still have flashbacks from strangers yelling "Innervate me!!" at them.

69762.name: Ironbeak Owl
69762.flavorText: Their wings are silent but their screech is... whatever the opposite of silent is.

69816.name: Jungle Panther
69816.flavorText: Stranglethorn is a beautiful place to visit, but you wouldn't want to live there.

69873.name: Keeper of the Grove
69873.text: Choose One - Deal 2 damage; or Silence a minion.
69873.flavorText: These guys just show up and start Keeping your Groves without even asking.

70075.name: Kidnapper
70075.text: Combo: Return a minion to its owner's hand.
70075.flavorText: He just wants people to see his vacation photos.

68472.name: Kill Command
68472.text: Deal 3 damage. If you control a Beast, deal 5 damage instead.

69968.name: King Krush
69968.flavorText: The best defense against King Krush is to have someone you don’t like standing in front of you.

69814.name: King Mukla
69814.flavorText: King Mukla wanders Jaguero Isle, searching for love.

70052.name: Kirin Tor Mage
70052.text: Battlecry: The next Secret you play this turn costs (0).
70052.flavorText: The Kirin Tor reside in the floating city of Dalaran. How do you make a Dalaran float? Two scoops of ice cream, one scoop of Dalaran.

70083.name: Knife Juggler
70083.text: After you summon a minion, deal 1 damage to a random enemy.
70083.flavorText: Ambitious Knife Jugglers sometimes graduate to Bomb Jugglers. They never last long enough to make it onto a card though.

68390.name: Kobold Geomancer
68390.flavorText: In the old days, Kobolds were the finest candle merchants in the land. Then they got pushed too far...

68528.name: Kor'kron Elite
68528.flavorText: The Kor'kron are the elite forces of Garrosh Hellscream. Let's just say you don't want to run into these guys while wearing a blue tabard.

69893.name: Lava Burst
69893.flavorText: It's like an ocean of liquid magma in your mouth!

69852.name: Leeroy Jenkins
69852.text: Charge. Battlecry: Summon two 1/1 Whelps for your opponent.
69852.flavorText: At least he has Angry Chicken.

69821.name: Leper Gnome
69821.text: Deathrattle: Deal 2 damage to the enemy hero.
69821.flavorText: He really just wants to be your friend, but the constant rejection is starting to really get to him.

68363.name: Light's Justice
68363.flavorText: Prince Malchezaar was a collector of rare weapons. He'd animate them and have them dance for him.

69892.name: Lightning Bolt
69892.flavorText: Lightning Bolt! Lightning Bolt! Lightning Bolt!

69902.name: Lightning Storm
69902.text: Deal 2- 3 damage to all enemy minions. Overload: (2)
69902.flavorText: An umbrella won't be effective, I'm afraid.

69928.name: Lightspawn
69928.text: This minion's Attack is always equal to its Health.
69928.flavorText: Spawn of the Light? Or Pawn of the Lights?

69804.name: Lightwarden
69804.text: Whenever a character is healed, gain +2 Attack.
69804.flavorText: She’s smaller than her sisters Mediumwarden and Heavywarden.

69930.name: Lightwell
69930.text: At the start of your turn, restore 3 Health to a damaged friendly character.
69930.flavorText: It isn't clear if people ignore the Lightwell, or if it is just invisible.

69925.name: Lord Jaraxxus
69925.text: Battlecry: Destroy your hero and replace it with Lord Jaraxxus.
69925.flavorText: "TRIFLING GNOME! YOUR ARROGANCE WILL BE YOUR UNDOING!!!!"

68394.name: Lord of the Arena
68394.flavorText: He used to be a 2100+ rated arena player, but that was years ago and nobody can get him to shut up about it.

69847.name: Lorewalker Cho
69847.text: Whenever a player casts a spell, put a copy into the other player’s hand.
69847.flavorText: Lorewalker Cho archives and shares tales from the land of Pandaria, but his favorite story is the one where Joey and Phoebe go on a road trip.

69838.name: Mad Bomber
69838.text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage randomly split between all other characters.
69838.flavorText: He's not really all that crazy, he is just not as careful with explosives as he should be.

68379.name: Magma Rager
68379.flavorText: He likes to think he is powerful, but pretty much anyone can solo Molten Core now.

69979.name: Malygos
69979.flavorText: Malygos hates it when mortals use magic. He gets so mad!

69831.name: Mana Addict
69831.text: Whenever you cast a spell, gain +2 Attack this turn.
69831.flavorText: She’s trying to kick the habit, but still takes some mana whenever she has a stressful day.

70032.name: Mana Tide Totem
70032.text: At the end of your turn, draw a card.
70032.flavorText: It is said that some shaman can say "Floatin' totem" 10 times, fast.

70055.name: Mana Wraith
70055.flavorText: They come out at night to eat leftover mana crystals. "Mmmmmm," they say.

70079.name: Mana Wyrm
70079.text: Whenever you cast a spell, gain +1 Attack.
70079.flavorText: These wyrms feed on arcane energies, and while they are generally considered a nuisance rather than a real threat, you really shouldn't leave them alone with a bucket of mana.

69866.name: Mark of Nature
69866.text: Choose One - Give a minion +4 Attack; or +4 Health and Taunt.
69866.flavorText: Druids call it the "Mark of Nature." Everyone else calls it "needing a bath."

68311.name: Mark of the Wild
68311.text: Give a minion Taunt and +2/+2. (+2 Attack/+2 Health)
68311.flavorText: Not to be confused with Jim of the Wild.

70063.name: Mass Dispel
70063.text: Silence all enemy minions. Draw a card.
70063.flavorText: It dispels buffs, powers, hopes, and dreams.

70095.name: Master Swordsmith
70095.text: At the end of your turn, give another random friendly minion +1 Attack.
70095.flavorText: He's currently trying to craft a "flail-axe", but all the other swordsmiths say it can't be done.

70080.name: Master of Disguise
70080.flavorText: She's actually a male tauren. People don't call him "Master of Disguise" for nothing.

68537.name: Mind Blast
68537.text: Deal 5 damage to the enemy hero.
68537.flavorText: This spell blasts you directly in the MIND.

68300.name: Mind Control
68300.text: Take control of an enemy minion.
68300.flavorText: Nominated as "Spell Most Likely to Make Your Opponent Punch the Wall."

69840.name: Mind Control Tech
69840.text: Battlecry: If your opponent has 4 or more minions, take control of one at random.
69840.flavorText: Mind Control technology is getting better, but that's not saying much.

68303.name: Mind Vision
68303.text: Put a copy of a random card in your opponent's hand into your hand.
68303.flavorText: I see what you did there.

69931.name: Mindgames
69931.text: Put a copy of a random minion from your opponent's deck into the battlefield.
69931.flavorText: Sometimes it feels like this is all a game.

69910.name: Mirror Entity
69910.text: Secret: When your opponent plays a minion, summon a copy of it.
69910.flavorText: "You go first." - Krush'gor the Behemoth, to his pet boar.

68325.name: Mirror Image
68325.flavorText: Oh hey it's Mirror Image! !egamI rorriM s'ti yeh hO

69963.name: Misdirection
69963.text: Secret: When an enemy attacks your hero, instead it attacks another random character.
69963.flavorText: Sometimes it's as simple as putting on a fake mustache and pointing at someone else.

69948.name: Mogu'shan Warden
69948.flavorText: All these guys ever do is talk about the Thunder King. BOOOORRRINNG!

70058.name: Molten Giant
70058.text: Costs (1) less for each damage your hero has taken.
70058.flavorText: He gets terrible heartburn. BECAUSE HE IS FULL OF LAVA.

68310.name: Moonfire
68310.flavorText: "Cast Moonfire, and never stop." - How to Be a Druid, Chapter 5, Section 3

68459.name: Mortal Coil
68459.text: Deal 1 damage to a minion. If that kills it, draw a card.
68459.flavorText: If your spells look like horrifying skulls, let's be honest, you should get to draw some cards.

69953.name: Mortal Strike
69953.text: Deal 4 damage. If you have 12 or less Health, deal 6 instead.
69953.flavorText: "If you only use one ability, use Mortal Strike." - The Warrior Code, Line 6

69850.name: Mountain Giant
69850.text: Costs (1) less for each other card in your hand.
69850.flavorText: His mother said that he was just big boned.

68432.name: Multi-Shot
68432.text: Deal 3 damage to two random enemy minions.

68395.name: Murloc Raider
68395.flavorText: Mrrraggglhlhghghlgh, mrgaaag blarrghlgaahahl mrgggg glhalhah a bghhll graggmgmg Garrosh mglhlhlh mrghlhlhl!!

69960.name: Murloc Tidecaller
69960.text: Whenever a Murloc is summoned, gain +1 Attack.
69960.flavorText: This guy gets crazy strong at family reunions.

69959.name: Murloc Warleader
69959.flavorText: Do Murlocs ever get tired of making the same old sound? Nope! Mrglglrglglglglglglgl!

69973.name: Nat Pagle
69973.text: At the start of your turn, you have a 50% chance to draw an extra card.
69973.flavorText: Nat Pagle, Azeroth's premier fisherman! He invented the Auto-Angler 3000, the Extendo-Pole 3000, and the Lure-o-matic 2099 (still in testing).

69869.name: Naturalize
69869.text: Destroy a minion. Your opponent draws 2 cards.

68478.name: Nightblade
68478.flavorText: Your face is the place you'd probably least like a dagger, and where rogues are most likely to deliver them.

69856.name: Noble Sacrifice
69856.text: Secret: When an enemy attacks, summon a 2/1 Defender as the new target.

68535.name: Northshire Cleric
68535.text: Whenever a minion is healed, draw a card.
68535.flavorText: They help the downtrodden and distressed. Also they sell cookies.

69871.name: Nourish
69871.text: Choose One - Gain 2 Mana Crystals; or Draw 3 cards.
69871.flavorText: Druids take nourishment from many things: the power of nature, the songbird's chirp, a chocolate cake.

68436.name: Novice Engineer
68436.flavorText: "Half of this class will not graduate… since they'll have been turned to chickens." - Tinkmaster Overspark, teaching Gizmos 101.

69976.name: Nozdormu
69976.text: Players only have 15 seconds to take their turns.
69976.flavorText: Time to write some flavor text.

68380.name: Oasis Snapjaw
68380.flavorText: His dreams of flying and breathing fire like his idol will never be realized.

68405.name: Ogre Magi
68405.flavorText: Training Ogres in the art of spellcasting is a questionable decision.

68538.name: Old Murk-Eye
68538.text: Charge. Has +1 Attack for each other Murloc on the battlefield.
68538.flavorText: He's a legend among murlocs. "Mrghllghghllghg!", they say.

69978.name: Onyxia
69978.text: Battlecry: Summon 1/1 Whelps until your side of the battlefield is full.
69978.flavorText: Onyxia long manipulated the Stormwind Court by disguising herself as Lady Katrana Prestor. You would have thought that the giant wings and scales would have been a giveaway.

69961.name: Patient Assassin
69961.text: Stealth. Destroy any minion damaged by this minion.
69961.flavorText: He’s not really that patient. It just takes a while for someone to walk by that he can actually reach.

69859.name: Perdition's Blade
69859.flavorText: Perdition's Blade is Ragnaros's back-up weapon while Sulfuras is in the shop.

69836.name: Pint-Sized Summoner
69836.text: The first minion you play each turn costs (1) less.
69836.flavorText: She's quite jealous of the Gallon-Sized Summoner.

69919.name: Pit Lord
69919.flavorText: Mannoroth, Magtheridon, and Brutallus may be dead, but it turns out there are a LOT of pit lords.

68319.name: Polymorph
68319.text: Transform a minion into a 1/1 Sheep.
68319.flavorText: There was going to be a pun in this flavor text, but it just came out baa-d.

69921.name: Power Overwhelming
69921.text: Give a friendly minion +4/+4 until end of turn. Then, it dies. Horribly.
69921.flavorText: We cannot even describe how horrible the death is. It's CRAZY bad! Maybe worse than that. Just don't do it.

68304.name: Power Word: Shield
68304.text: Give a minion +2 Health. Draw a card.
68304.flavorText: Sure the extra protection is nice, but the shield really reduces visibility.

69868.name: Power of the Wild
69868.text: Choose One - Give your minions +1/+1; or Summon a 3/2 Panther.
69868.flavorText: Never look a panther in the eye. Or is it 'Always look a panther in the eye'? Well, it's one of those.

69864.name: Preparation
69864.text: The next spell you cast this turn costs (3) less.

70035.name: Priestess of Elune
70035.flavorText: If she threatens to "moon" you, it's not what you think.

69933.name: Prophet Velen
69933.text: Double the damage and healing of your spells and Hero Power.
69933.flavorText: He's been exiled from his home, and all his brothers turned evil, but otherwise he doesn't have a lot to complain about.

69905.name: Pyroblast
69905.flavorText: Take the time for an evil laugh after you draw this card.

69825.name: Questing Adventurer
69825.text: Whenever you play a card, gain +1/+1.
69825.flavorText: "Does anyone have some extra Boar Pelts?"

69957.name: Raging Worgen
69957.flavorText: If he's raging now, just wait until he gets nerfed.

69912.name: Ragnaros the Firelord
69912.text: Can't attack. At the end of your turn, deal 8 damage to a random enemy.
69912.flavorText: Ragnaros was summoned by the Dark Iron dwarves, who were eventually enslaved by the Firelord. Summoning Ragnaros often doesn’t work out the way you want it to.

69758.name: Ravenholdt Assassin
69758.flavorText: Just mail him a package with a name and 10,000 gold. He'll take care of the rest.

68404.name: Razorfen Hunter
68404.flavorText: Someone did mess with Tuskerr once. ONCE.

68408.name: Reckless Rocketeer
68408.flavorText: One Insane Rocketeer. One Rocket full of Explosives. Infinite Fun.

69861.name: Redemption
69861.text: Secret: When a friendly minion dies, return it to life with 1 Health.
69861.flavorText: I am not sure how you get demptioned the first time. It’s a mystery!

69940.name: Repentance
69940.text: Secret: After your opponent plays a minion, reduce its Health to 1.
69940.flavorText: Repentance often comes in the moment before obliteration. Curious.

68381.name: River Crocolisk
68381.flavorText: Edward "Lefty" Smith tried to make luggage out of a river crocolisk once.

68334.name: Rockbiter Weapon
68334.text: Give a friendly character +3 Attack this turn.
68334.flavorText: This would be real handy if your enemy is made of rock.

69860.name: SI:7 Agent
69860.flavorText: The agents of SI:7 are responsible for Stormwind's covert activities. Their duties include espionage, assassination, and throwing surprise birthday parties for the royal family.

68526.name: Sacrificial Pact
68526.text: Destroy a Demon. Restore 5 Health to your hero.
68526.flavorText: This is the reason that Demons never really become friends with Warlocks.

68475.name: Sap
68475.text: Return an enemy minion to your opponent's hand.

68313.name: Savage Roar
68313.text: Give your characters +2 Attack this turn.
68313.flavorText: What do they roar? Nobody can quite tell, but it sounds like "Elephant Macho Breeze". It's probably not that, though.

70034.name: Savagery
70034.text: Deal damage equal to your hero's Attack to a minion.
70034.flavorText: It is true that some druids are savage, but others still enjoy a quiet moment and a spot of tea.

69964.name: Savannah Highmane
69964.flavorText: In the jungle, the mighty jungle, the lion gets slowly consumed by hyenas.

69817.name: Scarlet Crusader
69817.flavorText: Never wash your whites with a Scarlet Crusader.

69962.name: Scavenging Hyena
69962.text: Whenever a friendly Beast dies, gain +2/+1.
69962.flavorText: Hyenas prefer the bones of kodos or windserpents, but they'll eat pretty much anything. Even Brussels sprouts.

70037.name: Sea Giant
70037.text: Costs (1) less for each other minion on the battlefield.

69837.name: Secretkeeper
69837.flavorText: Where is Mankrik’s wife? She’ll never tell.

68399.name: Sen'jin Shieldmasta
68399.flavorText: Sen'jin Village is nice, if you like trolls and dust.

69922.name: Sense Demons
69922.flavorText: Generally demons are pretty obvious and you don’t need a spell to sense them.

68341.name: Shadow Bolt
68341.flavorText: It’s a Bolt. It's made out of Shadow. What more do you need to know!

69927.name: Shadow Madness
69927.text: Gain control of an enemy minion with 3 or less Attack until end of turn.
69927.flavorText: You can rationalize it all you want, it's still a mean thing to do.

68480.name: Shadow Word: Death
68480.text: Destroy a minion with 5 or more Attack.
68480.flavorText: If you miss, it leaves a lightning-bolt-shaped scar on your target.

68414.name: Shadow Word: Pain
68414.text: Destroy a minion with 3 or less Attack.
68414.flavorText: A step up from a spell cast by many beginning acolytes: "Shadow Word: Annoy".

69914.name: Shadowflame
69914.text: Destroy a friendly minion and deal its Attack damage to all enemy minions.
69914.flavorText: Start with a powerful minion and stir in Shadowflame and you have a good time!

70062.name: Shadowform
70062.text: Your Hero Power becomes 'Deal 2 damage.' If already in Shadowform: 3 damage.
70062.flavorText: If a bright light shines on a priest in Shadowform… do they cast a shadow?

69863.name: Shadowstep
69863.text: Return a friendly minion to your hand. It costs (2) less.
69863.flavorText: Rogue dance troops will sometimes Shadowstep away at the end of a performance. Crowds love it.

68437.name: Shattered Sun Cleric
68437.flavorText: They always have a spare flask of Sunwell Energy Drink™!

68479.name: Shield Block
68479.flavorText: Shields were invented because Face Block is USELESS.

69955.name: Shield Slam
69955.text: Deal 1 damage to a minion for each Armor you have.
69955.flavorText: "What is a better weapon? The sharp one your enemies expect, or the blunt one they ignore?" - The Art of Warrior, Chapter 9

69951.name: Shieldbearer
69951.flavorText: Have you seen the size of the shields in this game?? This is no easy job.

69926.name: Silence
69926.flavorText: Reserved for enemy spellcasters, evil liches from beyond the grave, and karaoke nights at the Grim Guzzler.

69756.name: Silver Hand Knight
69756.flavorText: It's good to be a knight. Less so to be one's squire.

68387.name: Silverback Patriarch
68387.flavorText: He likes to act like he's in charge, but the silverback matriarch actually runs things.

69819.name: Silvermoon Guardian
69819.flavorText: The first time they tried to guard Silvermoon against the scourge, it didn’t go so well…

68351.name: Sinister Strike
68351.text: Deal 3 damage to the enemy hero.
68351.flavorText: There's something about this strike that just feels off. Sinister, even.

69916.name: Siphon Soul
69916.text: Destroy a minion. Restore 3 Health to your hero.
69916.flavorText: You probably should avoid siphoning your own soul. You might create some kind of weird infinite loop.

69945.name: Slam
69945.text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. If it survives, draw a card.
69945.flavorText: "Dun da dun, dun da dun": if you've heard an ogre sing this, it's too late.

69971.name: Snake Trap
69971.text: Secret: When one of your minions is attacked, summon three 1/1 Snakes.
69971.flavorText: Why did it have to be snakes?

70049.name: Snipe
70049.text: Secret: After your opponent plays a minion, deal 4 damage to it.
70049.flavorText: A great sniper hits the spot. Just like a delicious flank of boar. Mmmmm.

70048.name: Sorcerer's Apprentice
70048.flavorText: Apprentices are great for bossing around. "Conjure me some mana buns! And a coffee! Make that a mana coffee!"

69867.name: Soul of the Forest
69867.text: Give your minions "Deathrattle: Summon a 2/2 Treant."

68461.name: Soulfire
68461.text: Deal 4 damage. Discard a random card.
68461.flavorText: Are you lighting a soul on fire? Or burning someone with your OWN soul? This seems like an important distinction.

70091.name: Southsea Captain
70091.flavorText: When he saves enough plunder, he's going to commission an enormous captain's hat. He has hat envy.

69755.name: Southsea Deckhand
69755.text: Has Charge while you have a weapon equipped.
69755.flavorText: Pirates are into this new fad called "Planking".

70102.name: Spellbender
70102.text: Secret: When an enemy casts a spell on a minion, summon a 1/3 as the new target.
70102.flavorText: While it's fun to intercept enemy lightning bolts, a spellbender much prefers to intercept opposing Marks of the Wild. It just feels meaner. And blood elves... well, they're a little mean.

69828.name: Spellbreaker
69828.flavorText: Spellbreakers can rip enchantments from magic-wielders. The process is painless and can be performed on an outpatient basis.

69763.name: Spiteful Smith
69763.flavorText: She'll craft you a sword, but you'll need to bring her 5 Steel Ingots, 3 Motes of Earth, and the scalp of her last customer.

70098.name: Stampeding Kodo
70098.text: Battlecry: Destroy a random enemy minion with 2 or less Attack.
70098.flavorText: This Kodo is so big that he can stampede by himself.

70076.name: Starfall
70076.text: Choose One - Deal 5 damage to a minion; or 2 damage to all enemy minions.
70076.flavorText: Is the sky falling? Yes. Yes it is.

68446.name: Starfire
68446.flavorText: Balance is important to druids. This card is perfectly balanced.

68416.name: Starving Buzzard
68416.text: Whenever you summon a Beast, draw a card.
68416.flavorText: If you feed him, he loses his whole identity.

68392.name: Stormpike Commando
68392.flavorText: The Stormpike Commandos are demolition experts. They also bake a mean cupcake.

68409.name: Stormwind Champion
68409.flavorText: When Deathwing assaulted the capital, this soldier was the only member of his squad to survive. Now he's all bitter and stuff.

68388.name: Stormwind Knight
68388.flavorText: They're still embarrassed about "The Deathwing Incident".

69820.name: Stranglethorn Tiger
69820.flavorText: The wonderful thing about tigers is tigers are wonderful things!

69920.name: Summoning Portal
69920.text: Your minions cost (2) less, but not less than (1).
69920.flavorText: NOT LESS THAN 1! Don't get any ideas!

69833.name: Sunfury Protector
69833.flavorText: She carries a shield, but only so she can give it to someone she can stand behind.

69822.name: Sunwalker
69822.flavorText: She doesn’t ACTUALLY walk on the Sun. It's just a name. Don’t worry!

68315.name: Swipe
68315.text: Deal 4 damage to an enemy and 1 damage to all other enemies.
68315.flavorText: When a bear rears back and extends his arms, he's about to Swipe! ... or hug.

69939.name: Sword of Justice
69939.text: After you summon a minion, give it +1/+1 and this loses 1 Durability.
69939.flavorText: I dub you Sir Loin of Beef!

69815.name: Sylvanas Windrunner
69815.text: Deathrattle: Take control of a random enemy minion.
69815.flavorText: Sylvanas was turned into the Banshee Queen by Arthas, but he probably should have just killed her because it just pissed her off.

69944.name: Tauren Warrior
69944.flavorText: Tauren Warrior: Champion of Mulgore, Slayer of Quilboar, Rider of Thunderbluff Elevators.

70060.name: Temple Enforcer
70060.flavorText: He also moonlights Thursday nights as a bouncer at the Pig and Whistle Tavern.

70033.name: The Beast
70033.text: Deathrattle: Summon a 3/3 Pip Quickwit for your opponent.
70033.flavorText: He lives in Blackrock Mountain. He eats Gnomes. That's pretty much it.

69805.name: The Black Knight
69805.flavorText: He was sent by the Lich King to disrupt the Argent Tournament. We can pretty much mark that a failure.

69929.name: Thoughtsteal
69929.text: Copy 2 cards in your opponent's deck and add them to your hand.
69929.flavorText: "What do you get when you cast Thoughtsteal on an Orc? Nothing!" - Tauren joke

69818.name: Thrallmar Farseer
69818.flavorText: He's stationed in the Hellfire Peninsula, but he's hoping for a reassignment closer to Orgrimmar, or really anywhere the ground is less on fire.

68428.name: Timber Wolf
68428.flavorText: Other beasts totally dig hanging out with timber wolves.

69839.name: Tinkmaster Overspark
69839.text: Battlecry: Transform another random minion into a 5/5 Devilsaur or a 1/1 Squirrel.
69839.flavorText: Tinkmaster Overspark nearly lost his Tinker's license after the Great Ironforge Squirrel Stampede of '09.

69942.name: Tirion Fordring
69942.flavorText: If you haven't heard the Tirion Fordring theme song, it's because it doesn't exist.

68433.name: Tracking
68433.text: Look at the top 3 cards of your deck. Draw one and discard the others.
68433.flavorText: For the person who just cannot decide what card to put into a deck!

68368.name: Truesilver Champion
68368.text: Whenever your hero attacks, restore 2 Health to it.
68368.flavorText: It Slices, it Dices. You can cut a tin can with it. (But you wouldn't want to.)

68430.name: Tundra Rhino
68430.flavorText: Tundra rhinos are often mistaken for kodos. Or am I mistaken?

69824.name: Twilight Drake
69824.text: Battlecry: Gain +1 Health for each card in your hand.
69824.flavorText: Twilight drakes feed on Mystical Energy. And Tacos.

69918.name: Twisting Nether
69918.flavorText: The Twisting Nether is a formless place of magic and illusion and destroyed minions.

69901.name: Unbound Elemental
69901.text: Whenever you play a card with Overload, gain +1/+1.
69901.flavorText: Unlike bound elementals, Unbound ones really enjoy a night on the town.

69967.name: Unleash the Hounds
69967.text: For each enemy minion, summon a 1/1 Hound with Charge.
69967.flavorText: You must read the name of this card out loud each time you play it.

69954.name: Upgrade!
69954.text: If you have a weapon, give it +1/+1. Otherwise equip a 1/3 weapon.

68548.name: Vanish
68548.text: Return all minions to their owner's hand.

70040.name: Vaporize
70040.text: Secret: When a minion attacks your hero, destroy it.
70040.flavorText: Rumor has it that Deathwing brought about the Cataclysm after losing a game to this card. We may never know the truth.

69764.name: Venture Co. Mercenary
69764.flavorText: No Job is too big. No fee is too big.

70090.name: Violet Teacher
70090.text: Whenever you cast a spell, summon a 1/1 Violet Apprentice.
70090.flavorText: If you don't pay attention, you may be turned into a pig. And then you get your name on the board.

69915.name: Void Terror
69915.text: Battlecry: Destroy both adjacent minions and gain their Attack and Health.
69915.flavorText: If you put this into your deck, you WILL lose the trust of your other minions.

68347.name: Voidwalker
68347.flavorText: No relation to "The Voidsteppers", the popular Void-based dance troupe.

68435.name: Voodoo Doctor
68435.flavorText: Voodoo is an oft-misunderstood art. But it is art.

68401.name: War Golem
68401.flavorText: Golems are not afraid, but for some reason they still run when you cast Fear on them. Instinct, maybe? A desire to blend in?

68442.name: Warsong Commander
68442.text: Whenever you summon a minion with 3 or less Attack, give it Charge.
68442.flavorText: The Warsong clan is such drama. It's really not worth it to become a commander.

68328.name: Water Elemental
68328.text: Freeze any character damaged by this minion.
68328.flavorText: Don't summon a water elemental at a party. It'll dampen the mood.

68467.name: Whirlwind
68467.flavorText: The way to tell seasoned warriors from novice ones: the novices yell "wheeeee" while whirlwinding.

68316.name: Wild Growth
68316.flavorText: Grow your own mana crystals with this Mana Crystal Growth Kit, only 39.99!

70084.name: Wild Pyromancer
70084.text: After you cast a spell, deal 1 damage to ALL minions.
70084.flavorText: BOOM BABY BOOM! BAD IS GOOD! DOWN WITH GOVERNMENT!

68330.name: Windfury
68330.flavorText: Windfury is like Earthfury and Firefury, but more light and airy.

69823.name: Windfury Harpy
69823.flavorText: Harpies are not pleasant sounding. That's the nicest I can put it.

68477.name: Windspeaker
68477.flavorText: Is there anything worse than a Windspeaker with halitosis?

69765.name: Wisp
69765.flavorText: If you hit an Eredar Lord with enough Wisps, it will explode. But why?

68385.name: Wolfrider
68385.flavorText: Orcish raiders ride wolves because they are well adapted to harsh environments, and because they are soft and cuddly.

69812.name: Worgen Infiltrator
69812.flavorText: If you want to stop a worgen from infiltrating, just yell, "No! Bad boy!"

69865.name: Wrath
69865.text: Choose One - Deal 3 damage to a minion; or 1 damage and draw a card.
69865.flavorText: The talk around the Ratchet Inn is that this card is too good and should be a Legendary.

69759.name: Young Dragonhawk
69759.flavorText: They were the inspiration for the championship Taurenball team: The Dragonhawks.

69806.name: Young Priestess
69806.text: At the end of your turn, give another random friendly minion +1 Health.
69806.flavorText: She can't wait to learn Power Word: Fortitude Rank 2.

69829.name: Youthful Brewmaster
69829.text: Battlecry: Return a friendly minion from the battlefield to your hand.
69829.flavorText: His youthful enthusiasm doesn’t always equal excellence in his brews. Don’t drink the Mogu Stout!

70980.name: Ysera
70980.text: At the end of your turn, add a Dream Card to your hand.
70980.flavorText: Ysera rules the Emerald Dream. Which is some kind of green-mirror-version of the real world, or something?
